cyclone.name: ZETA
cyclone.current_location: about 305 mi south-southeast of the western tip of Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: Expected to resume a slow north-northwest to northwest motion today, turn west-northwest and cross the northern Yucatan Peninsula late Monday, then accelerate northwestward across the central Gulf of Mexico toward the central Gulf Coast by Wednesday.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: central Gulf Coast near the Louisiana/Mississippi shoreline

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Watch from Tulum to Rio Lagartos (Yucatan) and Cozumel, Mexico
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning for Pinar del Río Province, Cuba
weather_observation.impacted_coast: northern Yucatan Peninsula Monday, then northern Gulf Coast from Louisiana to Alabama by mid-week
weather_observation.closest_wind_data_location: Not available (Wilmington, DE not listed in wind-probability table)
weather_observation.wind: Breezy conditions possible late Thursday–Friday as the remnant system passes inland, but tropical-storm-force winds are unlikely (<34 kt).
weather_observation.storm_surge: None expected along the Delaware coast from Zeta.
weather_observation.rainfall: Remnant moisture could bring 1–2 inches of rain to the Delaware River Valley late week, producing localized ponding.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Low chance of isolated brief tornadoes if the remnant circulation tracks directly overhead.
